ness.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;In regard to search radius we suggest to use at least 3 pixels.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</summary><usage>&lt;DIV STYLE="text-align:Left;"&gt;&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Define input raster, lag and search window radius. The function returns 3 raster&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;s&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;: 1) Omnidirectional/isotropic MAD; 2) Direction of maximum continuity and 3) Anisotropy index&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;(0 no anisotropy, 1 maximum anisotropy).&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</usage></tool><dataIdInfo><idCitation><resTitle>MadScan</resTitle></idCitation><resConst><Consts><useLimit>&lt;DIV STYLE="text-align:Left;"&gt;&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Spatial Anal&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;y&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;st required&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN /&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;The software is furnished without any warranty! See MADfunctionsV1.py for details on license and disclaimer&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</useLimit></Consts></resConst><dataExt><geoEle xmlns=""><GeoBndBox esriExtentType="search"/></geoEle></dataExt><idAbs>&lt;DIV STYLE="text-align:Left;"&gt;&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;This function permits calculation of basics surface texture indexes based on MAD estimator. The available lags are: 2,4,6, and 8 pixels.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Omnidirectional/isotropic MAD for lag 2 pixels can be used as a robust measure of surface roughness.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;In regard to search radius we suggest to use at least 3 pixels.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</idAbs><idCredit>"Trevisani S., Rocca M.,MAD: robust image texture analysis for applications in high resolution geomorphometry. Submitted to Computer &amp; Geosciences, 2014".</idCredit><searchKeys><keyword>Surface/i